Radiocarbon dates from Shubayqa 1

Source: R/data-examples.R
shub1_c14.Rd

Radiocarbon dates from Shubayqa 1, an Epipalaeolithic site in eastern Jordan, from Richter2017;textualc14.

Usage

shub1_c14

Format

A data frame with 27 rows and 8 variables:

lab_id

character; standardised lab code uniquely identifying the dated sample.

context

integer; schematic context number the sample was found in (see details).

phase

character; phase the sample was assigned to.

sample

character; description of the sample context, including its real context number.

material

character; description of the sample material.

c14_age

integer; conventional radiocarbon age of the sample in years cal BP.

c14_error

integer; standard error associated with the radiocarbon measurement in ± years cal BP.

outlier

logical; whether the sample is considered an outlier.

Source

Richter2017;textualc14

Details

context refers to the schematic stratigraphy included in stratigraphr::shub1; the real context number is described in sample.
